The paper discusses gender bias in citation practices in neuroscience, which involves analyzing data from journals and developing a co-authorship network. This suggests that the paper could fit into several arXiv CS sub-categories, including social and information sciences (cs.SI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), cybernetics (cs.CY), digital libraries (cs.DL), and computer engineering (cs.CE).
